content.protection: 6 bolts to 2 bolt anchor with chains

content.description:
Climbs on and to the right of the prominent gold streak.

20 feet of easy climbing brings you to the first bolt.  Well protected and high quality knobs to the top.

This route is dedicated to Roger Brown, workhorse of the ASCA. Brown's passion for drilling and bolting is neither matched nor understood by any man.
content.protection: 8 bolts to 2 bolt anchor with chains

content.description:
Techy knobs, to balancy traverse, to powerful jug pulling over a bulge, to keeping it together to the chains.  Sick.

Shares first bolt with Titty Twister.
content.protection: 8 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor with rings

content.description:
Rebolted by ASCA (Roger Brown) in 2018

Good route, More classic knob pulling.

A bit more heady at the crux than on the surrounding routes.

Named "Right" by Falkenstein due to it being the rightmost of the three original routes on the formation.  The first ascentionists' intended name is unknown.
content.protection: 6 bolts to 2 bolt anchor with chains

content.description:
Knob pulling glory.  Well protected climb that ascends solid golden rock.  One of the best climbs at the crag.

Shares first bolt with Saving Grace and anchor with Kill Bill.
